'''Shintō Taikyō''' (神道大教), formerly called '''Shinto Honkyoku''' (神道本局), is a Japanese [[Shintoism|Shintoist]] organization, and was established by Meiji officials in 1873.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20030921080618/http://www.adherents.com/Na/Na_602.html Article Title]</ref> It is recognized officially,<ref>http://www.joyofsects.com/world/shinto.shtml</ref> and its headquarters are in [[Tokyo]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://eos.kokugakuin.ac.jp/modules/xwords/entry.php?entryID=652|title = Encyclopedia of Shinto - Home : Modern Sectarian Groups : Shintō Taikyō}}</ref> It has many shrines,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.novelguide.com/a/discover/ear_01/ear_01_00184.html |title=Shintoism |website=www.novelguide.com |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091031133529/http://www.novelguide.com/a/discover/ear_01/ear_01_00184.html |archive-date=2009-10-31}}</ref> and [[Tenrikyo]] used to be under its jurisdiction.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tenrikyo.or.jp/en/newsletter/html/tt5/genten_kyoten.html|title = Genten to kyoten}}</ref>

